column1: Rate of Rhode Island Residents Partially Vaccinated per 100,000 Population by Age Group and Week

Source: Rhode Island Department of Health (RIDOH); Rhode Island Child and Adult Immunization Registry (RICAIR); US Census Bureau 2018 annual estimates by single year of age (population by age group) and 2018 American Community Survey 5-year estimates (total population)

NOTES: Congregate setting residents are included. Out-of-state residents are excluded. 
 Rates based on small numbers (<5) are shown as *, in line with RIDOH's Small Numbers Policy. We provide weekly data to help show broader trends over time. Fluctuations in these data may be due to a variety of factors, such as vaccine availability and eligibility criteria. Please use caution when interpreting these data.
